.TH ROSIE 1
.SH NAME
rosie \- generate shell commands from natural-language prompts or answer questions in chat mode
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rosie
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIPROMPT\fR]...
.IB --chat,-c
[ \fI--model MODE\fR | \fI-MODEL=MODE\fR ] [ \fI-PROMPT PROM\fR ]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rosie
takes a natural-language task description, sends it to an OpenAI-compatible
chat completion endpoint, and returns the resulting shell command with a short
summary. Alternatively, when run in
.I --chat
mode (or with \fB\-c\fR), it answers general questions naturally without generating commands. Chat mode is non-interactive - the answer is printed once and the program exits.
.PP
Prompts can be passed as trailing arguments or via standard input. When run in
an interactive terminal without a prompt argument,
.B rosie
asks for one before sending the request. In chat mode, you can re-enter questions
until quitting.
.PP
After showing the generated command and summary, interactive mode offers
.B execute,
.B re-enter prompt,
or
.B quit.
Non-interactive mode prints the command and summary and then exits.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-configure
Interactively create or update the local configuration file. The command now performs 
automatic model discovery after setting the endpoint. When discovered, you can select from 
available models by number or full ID; if discovery fails, a default model is used instead.
.TP
.B \-\-install
Install the current binary into the local bin directory and install this man
page into the local man directory when available.
.TP
.BI --chat,-c [ \fI--model MODE\fR ]
Run in chat mode to answer general questions instead of generating shell commands.
Note: Chat mode is non-interactive - returns a simple text answer without formatting
or interactive options (no execute, re-enter, or quit). Optional model override (defaults to gpt-4o-mini).
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print help information.
.TP
.IB -V,--version
Display version information and exit.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Rosie reads configuration in this order:
.IP "1." 4
Environment variables
.IP "2." 4
Local config file at
.I ~/.config/rosie/config.toml
.IP "3." 4
Built-in defaults
.PP
Recognized environment variables:
.TP
.B ROSIE_API_KEY
API key for the OpenAI-compatible endpoint. Required for non-local endpoints.
For localhost endpoints, Rosie falls back to a built-in dummy key if unset.
.TP
.B ROSIE_ENDPOINT
Base endpoint URL. Defaults to
.I https://api.openai.com
.
.TP
.B ROSIE_MODEL
Model name. Defaults to
.I gpt-4o-mini
.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/rosie/config.toml
Persistent local configuration written by
.BR rosie " "--configure .
Stores endpoint URL, model name, and optional dummy-key allowlist entries.
.TP
.I ~/.local/bin/rosie
Default install location for the executable when
.B XDG_BIN_HOME
is unset.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/man/man1/rosie.1
Default install location for the man page when
.B XDG_DATA_HOME
is unset.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Configure Rosie:
.B rosie \-\-configure
.TP
Install Rosie:
.B rosie \-\-install
.TP
Generate a command from arguments:
.B rosie show me the top 10 processes by memory usage
.TP
Prompt interactively and then choose whether to execute:
.B rosie
.TP
Run in chat mode for general Q&A:
.B rosie --chat "What's the capital of France?"
.TP
Generate a command from standard input:
.B echo "list all git branches" | rosie
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B rosie
exits with status 0 on success and non-zero on error.
